<body>
    <img src="img/logoo.png" id="logo">
    <h1>Terms and Conditions</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>Eligibility: Participation in the scout program is open to individuals of all genders, ages, and backgrounds. However, minors under the age of 18 must have parental or guardian consent to participate.</li>
        <li>Code of Conduct: Scouts are expected to conduct themselves in a respectful and responsible manner at all times. This includes treating fellow scouts, leaders, and members of the community with courtesy and kindness.</li>
        <li>Safety: Safety is our top priority. Scouts must adhere to all safety guidelines provided by the scout organization and its leaders. This includes following instructions during activities, wearing appropriate safety gear, and reporting any hazards or concerns promptly.</li>
        <li>Attendance: Scouts are expected to attend regular meetings, events, and activities as scheduled by the scout organization. If unable to attend, scouts should notify their troop leader or designated contact in advance.</li>
        <li>Uniform and Equipment: Scouts are required to wear the official scout uniform during designated events and activities unless otherwise specified. Additionally, scouts must take care of any equipment or materials provided by the scout organization and return them in good condition.</li>
        <li>Respect for Nature: Scouts should demonstrate respect for the environment and wildlife during outdoor activities. This includes proper disposal of waste, leaving natural habitats undisturbed, and following Leave No Trace principles.</li>
        <li>Confidentiality: Scouts may have access to confidential information or personal details about other scouts or leaders. It is important to respect privacy and maintain confidentiality at all times.</li>
        <li>Communication: Scouts are encouraged to communicate openly and honestly with their troop leaders, fellow scouts, and scout organization representatives. Any concerns or feedback should be addressed through appropriate channels.</li>
        <li>Parental Involvement: Parents or guardians play an important role in supporting their child's participation in the scout program. They are encouraged to stay informed about scout activities, provide transportation when necessary, and participate in parent meetings or events.</li>
        <li>Disciplinary Action: Violation of these terms and conditions, as well as any other rules or policies established by the scout organization, may result in disciplinary action. This could include suspension or expulsion from the scout program.</li>
    </ol>
    <img src="img/terms.png" id="terms">

</body>
</html>